# Repository boundaries

## Default deny

Unless Operator mission explicitly authorizes it, do not:

- Modify product source under `src/`, `worker/`, `shared/`, or build configs
- `git commit`, `git push`, `git pull`, `git merge`, `git rebase`, destructive resets/cleans
- Create or modify PRs; deploy (`wrangler deploy`); change secrets; apply migrations; access production

## Preserve state

- Leave unrelated and dirty-tree changes untouched
- Do not stage, revert, or “clean up” files outside mission scope
- Keep `.cursor/agents/FLYWHEEL_RELEASE_CANDIDATE_OPERATOR.md` unless Operator says otherwise

## Secrets and generated noise

- Never read aloud or rewrite `.dev.vars`, `.env*`, wrangler secrets, or credential files
- Prefer excluding generated/local paths via `.cursorignore` / `.gitignore` conventions

## Phase 1 bootstrap note

Engineering Division bootstrap may edit only the ten approved Cursor instruction files when Operator authorizes that mission.
